distorOrdPrc.ordInstr: Custom Order Process: Upon compliance with level 3 of the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files, this data will be made available for download on the MassGIS website: http://www.mass.gov/anf/research-and-tech/it-serv-and-support/application-serv/office-of-geographic-information-massgis/datalayers/l3parcels.html; Technical Prerequisites: GIS software

onLineSrc.orDesc: Click on the "Download this layer" link to access all digital parcels.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset is a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of Hanson, Massachusetts. Edits to a base parcel file were made to the spatial and tabular data in order to bring the file in compliance with November 2010 MassGIS Level III Standards for Digital Parcel Files. These edits included ensuring that the parcel fabric was continuous and closed with no gaps or overlaps. Additionally, parcels were snapped to the legislatively approved MassGIS TOWNSSURVEY_ARC town boundary datalayer and compared against the 2008 30 cm MassGIS Ortho Imagery. Polygons were assigned a LOC_ID that links to the M131Assessor table and other fields were populated where they were known and applicable. Annual parcel updates completed February 2024. Geometry and attribute data updated on October 2024.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Parcel mapping data maintained by CAI Technologies

Consts.useLimit: This data may be appropriate for planning purposes. It should not be utilized where legal and surveyed property boundaries are required.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: The purpose of this dataset is to provide the Massachuesetts Office of Geographic Information with a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of Hanson, Massachuesetts that comply with its Level III standards.

prcStep.stepDesc: Parcel polygons and water, wetland and ROW lines converted with ESRI tools to project, dissolve, copy, calculate, and generally manipulate the ESRI version of the data to meet Mass GIS Level III standards. The source data is not changed by this process.

dataSource.srcDesc: This GIS dataset represents a digital version of assessor tax maps that were previously converted and processed into a GIS file which is used to produce the paper Tax Maps for the community. Original mapping compiled existing paper tax maps.

overview.dsoverv: M123TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of HANSON that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M123Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M123OthLeg and M123Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http:/ /www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
